yisraÚel veÚal yerusha/UNla/XXyim./PR
/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. As we enter the dark of evening, we face the unknown. Earlier,
in /ITAsher Bidvaro/XX (the Creation section immediately following /ITBareh/±u/XX), we
affirmed the power that transforms night into day and day into night. Now
we call for protection from the shadows that lengthen around us--shadows
of fear and guilt, the uncharted future, the ever pursuing past. We ask that
the shadows of GodÚs wings envelop us with love and mercy. The
unknown night, like the unknown tomorrow, can only be met with faith
in the power of infinite compassion to care for us.    /SC/XXS.P.W./XX/PR
/PR
