/PG88/XX/PR
/KAINTRODUCTIONS TO THE AMIDAH/XX/PR
Standing here in AbrahamÚs desert/PR
Affirming: one God./PR
/PR
Moving in the old spaces/PR
Warmed by our ancestorsÚ embrace./PR
/PR
Standing here in SarahÚs tent/PR
Laughing: new life./PR
/PR
Moving in the old spaces/PR
Renewed by our ancestorsÚ hope./PR
/PR
Standing here in my place/PR
Listening to our voices: yearning./PR
/PR
Moving in my own spaces/PR
Translating the silence./PR
Sandy Eisenberg Sasso/XX/PR
* */PR
Dear God,/PR
Open the blocked passageways to you,/PR
The congealed places./PR
/PR
Roll away the heavy stone from the well as your servant/PR
Jacob did when he beheld his beloved Rachel./PR
/PR
Help us open the doors of trust that have been jammed with/PR
hurt and rejection./PR
/PR
As you open the blossoms in spring,/PR
Even as you open the heavens in storm,/PR
Open us--to feel your great, awesome, wonderful presence./PR
Sheila Peltz Weinberg/XX/PR
/PR
/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. Prayer is communion. To commune with God is to put oneself
in touch with the source of cosmic energy.    /SC/XXM.M.K./XX/PR
